Code Kata based on Growing Object Oriented software by Tests - Nat pryce, Steve Freeman

Different approach to the problem
Focus is not on UI

A fictionary AuctionHouse conducts online Auctions. Clients may bid for items.
AuctionHouse broadcasts auction events to clients
Each auction is unique and is determined by the identity of the item it is selling

Clients can subscribe to multiple auctions,
set autobids - where bids happen automatically at a higher price until a stop-price

Tasks
 1. Join the auction process, do nothing
 2. Join and listen to bids
 3. Join and bid some item and loose the bid
 4. Join, Bid and Win
 5. Join, AutoBid and loose
 6. Join, AutoBid and Win

